Package: grase
Title: Graph of Alternative Splice Junctions and Exonic Parts
Version: 0.99.0
Authors@R:
    person("Mira", "Han", , "mira.han@unlv.edu", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-0488-1170"))
Description: GrASE bridges the gap between splice-junction-based differential
    splicing tools and exon-fragment-based tools by constructing splicing graphs from transcript annotations.
    The package represents each gene as a directed acyclic graph of splice
    junctions and exonic parts, enumerates transcript paths through the
    graph, and identifies "bubbles" (alternative splicing events) as
    subgraphs between shared source and sink nodes. It supports binary
    (bipartition) and multinomial groupings of transcript paths, tests for
    differential exon usage with beta-binomial and generalized linear mixed
    models, and maps results between the two analysis frameworks to provide
    a unified view of alternative splicing.
